## Traps

- Prism's `DataSource<T>` fixes TId to `string` even though the
  underlying `DataTableAdapter<T, TId>` accepts a typed TId. Numeric
  PKs require stringifying at `getRowId`. Documented as G-1.
- `useRouter` from `next/navigation` is the right way to handle
  `onRowClick` navigation; `window.location.assign` causes a full
  page reload and loses Next router state.
- Adapter recreations on filter-state change DO trigger engine
  refetch (engine's useEffect dep includes `adapter` identity). To
  avoid backend re-hits, cache the raw API response at the page
  level and have the adapter close over the cached array.
- `onExecute: async (...)` puts the row-action button into a busy
  state automatically — no manual `downloadingId` state needed.
- arbor consumes Prism via `/tmp/kailash-prism-web-*.tgz`. Re-pack
  after every Prism change. This still hurts; G-2-adjacent.
- `display="card-grid"` mode wires `onRowClick` to Card's `onActivate`,
  preserving row-click navigation parity. Worth a one-liner in the
  Prism CHANGELOG; documented as G-5.
